# Settings (storage + authoring)

Cross-cut with `30-mv3-messaging-architecture.mdc`. End-to-end flow: **defaults → merge in `settings.service.js` → `GET_SETTINGS` / `SAVE_SETTINGS` / `RESET_SETTINGS` → viewer/options/popup via `sendMessage()`.**

## Storage and schema

- Keep settings ownership centralized in `src/settings/settings.service.js` (load/merge/save/reset).
- Persist only with keys from `src/settings/storage-keys.js` (currently `mdViewer.settings`).
- Preserve default-safe loading with `deepMerge(DEFAULT_SETTINGS, raw)` so new keys get sane defaults.
- If schema changes incompatibly, bump `settings.version` in `default-settings.js` and add an explicit migration in `settings.service.js` (do not rely on merge alone).
- `popup` and `options` must use runtime messaging (`MESSAGE_TYPES` + `sendMessage`); **never** read/write `chrome.storage` directly from those pages.

## Adding or changing a setting

### Schema and defaults

- Add or extend fields in `src/settings/default-settings.js`. New nested objects should have complete default shapes so merge stays safe.
- Read/write storage stays only in `settings.service.js`.

### Messaging

- Prefer **partial updates** with existing `MESSAGE_TYPES.SAVE_SETTINGS` and the `{ ok, data }` / `{ ok, error }` envelope.
- Add a new `MESSAGE_TYPES` value only when not expressible as save/get/reset; register it in `src/background/message-router.js`.
- UIs use `sendMessage()` from `src/messaging/send-message.js`, not raw `chrome.runtime.sendMessage`.

### Viewer settings UI (tabs)

- **Tab list**: `src/viewer/shell/settings/settings-tab-definitions.js` (`SETTINGS_TAB_IDS`, `SETTINGS_TABS`).
- **Orchestration**: `src/viewer/shell/settings/settings-popup.js` (`createSettingsDrawer`) — rail, outside-dismiss, tab panels.
- **Per-tab content**: new module under `src/viewer/shell/settings/` exporting a builder like `buildGeneralSettingsPanel`: `{ element, update(nextSettings), destroy() }`.
- Wire the tab in `settings-popup.js`. **Styling**: `src/viewer/styles/settings.scss` (bundled via content script `?inline`); prefer extending theme CSS vars in `src/theme/` when possible.
- **Shell**: pass new props through `viewer-shell.js` only when `createSettingsDrawer` needs them (e.g. `settingsButton`).
- Public import path stays `src/viewer/shell/settings-drawer.js` (re-export).

### Applying in the viewer

- Live updates: `MarkdownViewerApp` / `createUpdateSettingsAction`; patches must match the persisted shape (merge → debounced persist).
- Prefer `applyThemeSettings` / `css-vars` for look-and-feel-only changes instead of duplicating CSS paths.

### Build

- After changes that affect packaged output, run `npm run build` (do not hand-edit `dist/**`).
